The ABTS assay of RFCS was performed according to a modified version of a previously reported method [19]. Briefly, the stock solutions were generated by mixing equal quantities of 7.4 mM ABTS●+ solution and 2.6 mM potassium persulfate solution, and the mixture was incubated at room temperature for 12 h in the dark. Then, the solution was equilibrated with 1 mL of ABTS●+ solution with 50% ethanol serving as a positive control. The absorbance of the solution at 734 nm was 1.17 ± 0.02 units. Aliquots (10 μL) of the rose samples (1000 μg/mL to 62.5 μg/mL) were mixed with 1.0 mL of the diluted ABTS•+ solution. The mixture was mixed vigorously and incubated at 30 °C for 30 min. The absorbance was then measured at 520 nm with an excitation wavelength of 734 nm using the spectrophotometer. The positive standard was Trolox (2000 μg/mL to 0.05 μg/mL).\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
